  "texts": [
    "Gloss-to-text recognitionDue to individual life habits and other reasons, Auslan users may have slight variations in their signing.",
    "At this point, a (1) similarity(v, e i) = v ⋅ e i ‖v‖‖e i ‖, deep learning network is required to adapt to these variations.",
    "Followed by [7,[16][17][18], we employ a two-stream network for isolated sign language recognition.",
    "For the pose stream, we initially utilise Alphapose [30], an accurate whole-body pose estimator, to extract the human 2D keypoints.",
    "Subsequently, the concatenation of all 2D keypoint coordinates in each frame is used as the input feature, and is then fed into the Sign Language Graph Convolution Network (SL-GCN) [16] for learning the pose sequence representation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
